Please translate each line literally into English and Sanskrit.

34 Ed elli a me: «La mia scrittura è piana;
35 e la speranza di costor non falla,
36 se ben si guarda con la mente sana;

37 ché cima di giudicio non s’avvalla
38 perché foco d’amor compia in un punto
39 ciò che de’ sodisfar chi qui s’astalla;

40 e là dov’ io fermai cotesto punto,
41 non s’ammendava, per pregar, difetto,
42 perché ’l priego da Dio era disgiunto.

query.result:
**English:**

34 And he to me: "My writing is plain;
35 and the hope of these people does not fail,
36 if it is well considered with a sound mind;

37 for the summit of judgment is not lowered
38 because the fire of love accomplishes in an instant
39 that which should satisfy him who settles here;

40 and there where I fixed that point,
41 no defect was amended by prayer,
42 because the prayer was disjoined from God.

**Sanskrit:**

34 Sa ca mama likhitam sulabham;
35 Na caivāsām āśā mithyā bhavati,
36 Yady api samyak avalokyate svacetasā;

37 Na hi nyūnam bhavati vivekasya śikharam
38 Yataḥ kāmasya agniḥ sampūrṇayati ekena kṣaṇena
39 Yat tatra tṛpyati yaḥ pratiṣṭhate;

40 Tatra ca yatra aham sthāpayāmi etad lakṣyam,
41 Na nivāryate doṣaḥ prārthanayā,
42 Yataḥ prārthanā Devāt praviyuktā.
